# wolfRadar — Railway + Vercel production setup
#
# ARCHITECTURE
#   Vercel (frontend)  →  STOCKY_BACKEND_URL  →  Railway API  →  SQLite on /data volume
#   Railway Cron (daily) →  same /data volume  →  refreshes snapshot
#
# ─── STEP 1: Railway API service ───
#
# 1. railway.app → New Project → Deploy from GitHub (wolfRadar repo)
# 2. Service name: api
# 3. Settings → Config-as-code path: railway.toml
# 4. Volumes → Add Volume → Mount path: /data
# 5. Variables:
#      WOLF_DATA_DIR=/data
#      NODE_ENV=production
# 6. Settings → Networking → Generate Domain
#    Example: https://wolfradar-api-production.up.railway.app
#
# ─── STEP 2: First snapshot (one time, ~1–2 hours) ───
#
# Install Railway CLI: npm i -g @railway/cli
# railway login
# railway link
# railway run --service api node scripts/bootstrap-snapshot.js
#
# Verify:
#   curl https://YOUR-API-DOMAIN/api/screener/status
#   → "rowCount": 6381
#
# ─── STEP 3: Railway Cron service (daily auto-refresh) ───
#
# 1. Same project → + New → Empty Service → name: snapshot-cron
# 2. Settings → Config-as-code path: railway.cron.toml
# 3. Attach SAME volume → mount /data  (critical!)
# 4. Variables: WOLF_DATA_DIR=/data, NODE_ENV=production
# 5. Cron runs Mon–Fri 11:00 UTC automatically
#
# ─── STEP 4: Vercel frontend ───
#
# Vercel project → Settings → Environment Variables:
#   STOCKY_BACKEND_URL=https://YOUR-API-DOMAIN
# (no trailing slash)
#
# Redeploy Vercel after saving.
#
# Verify:
#   curl https://YOUR-VERCEL-APP.vercel.app/api/screener/status
#   → same rowCount as Railway
#
# ─── LOCAL DOCKER TEST ───
#
# docker build -t wolfradar-api .
# docker run -p 3333:3333 -v wolfradar-data:/data wolfradar-api
